/*------------------------------------------------------------------ 
 MBlue Nav-Style Menubar Vista (Ver. 0.2.2)

Author: M.BLUE - Tested on: Firefox 3.0.3 - Last Update: 16.10.2008
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Description:
 1. Transforms the Menubar.
 2. Makes the ToolbarButtons Nav-Style.
 3. Can use Separator/Spacer to customize the buttons (read below).
 4. Supports SMALL and BIG ICONS.
 5. Fixes Download-Helper icon.
 6. Skins FoxClocks & ForecastFox.
 7. Highly Customizable.
 8. Integrates with the other Nav-Style styles.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Notes:
-Using other Styles/Extensions/Themes may change some margin/border
 settings, making the buttons not aligned.
 If so, try not using other styles that changes margins in the
 Menubar, and use the default firefox theme. 

-Works in the Menubar only.

-Some Ext. Icons may not work correctly.

-Some Extension Icons doesn't work well with separators, place them
 between other icons or spacers.

-Even if this style supports big icons, it works better with small
 ones, because the default big icons are too big to fit inside the
 buttons, so this style resizes them.

-If you want to use the Nav-Buttons (Back-Forward, Stop, Reload)
 inside the Menubar, you also need:
 1) Nav-Buttons Vista on XP (fix back/forward/dropmarker) [*]
 2) Combine Nav-Buttons Vista (fix & combine stop/reload) [*]
--------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Customize the Buttons:
 This style uses the Toolbar-Separator to add the L/R part of the
 button-image, and the Toolbar-Spacer to create the 2px margin
 between the buttons. Open the customize window, and follow these
 guidelines to place the items:

 Separator [RED]: Place this to the LEFT/RIGHT side of any buttons
                  to create the rounded edge.

 Spacer [GREEN]:  Place this between 2 buttons to create the 2px
                  margin like the Nav-Buttons.
                  Place this before/after a Separator to give the
                  buttons more space.

 Other Icons:     Place the icons with nothing in-between to make
                  them unite.

 Main-Menu:       This is the menu. You can place this anywhere.

 Extensions:      Extensions like FoxClocks & ForecastFox can be
                  placed anywhere in the Menubar.

 Example:

 [MENU] [GREEN] [EXT] [GREEN] [RED] [ICON] [GREEN] [ICON] [RED]

 Starting from the left there are:
 Menu, space, Extension (like FoxClocks), space, then there are 2
 icons which the first is rounded (left), and the second is
 separated by a 2px spacer and rounded (right).
--------------------------------------------------------------------
CUSTOMIZING:

 1. MAIN-MENU TEXT SETTINGS.
 2. NAV-STYLE ITEMS OPACITY.
 3. ICONS OPACITY.
 4. FOXCLOCK & FORECASTFOX BACKGROUND COLOR.
 5. FOXCLOCK & FORECASTFOX TEXT SETTINGS.
 6. FOXCLOCK & FORECASTFOX ICONS OPACITY.

> GO TO BOTTOM OF THE PAGE TO CUSTOMIZE
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Supported Extensions:
-FoxClocks, ForecastFox, DownloadHelper.
-Works with the default buttons (for the Nav-Buttons you need the
 Nav-Buttons styles [*]), and should support almost all additional
 extensions buttons.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Integrates with:
 MBlue Nav-Buttons Vista on XP [*]
 MBlue Combine Nav-Buttons Vista [*]
 MBlue Nav-Style Url-Bar Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Buttons Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Tabs Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Statusbar Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Throbber Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Bookmarks-Bar Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Awesome-Bar Vista
>MBlue Nav-Style Menubar Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Popup Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Sidebar Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Sidebar Vista (Downloads, Addons, Extensions)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Updates:
 16.10.2008 Ver. 0.2.2 = few fixes
 11.10.2008 Ver. 0.2.1 = few fixes
 06.10.2008 Ver. 0.2.0 = ready to release
 ...
 21.09.2008 Ver. 0.1.0 = temp version
------------------------------------------------------------------*/





